00:48:22.020 --> 00:48:22.419
Hi.

00:48:22.419 --> 00:48:22.979
Thank you.

00:48:22.979 --> 00:48:27.540
Yeah, I was just curious if you, because you have a lot of experience in organizational

00:48:27.540 --> 00:48:34.979
structures and things like that, if you have any thoughts on policy for AI in the current

00:48:34.979 --> 00:48:39.699
setting and also specifically thinking about, there's a lot of people in my company that are

00:48:41.139 --> 00:48:43.780
hesitant because of the environmental impact of AI.

00:48:44.419 --> 00:48:46.100
And so if you have anything specific on that.

00:48:47.540 --> 00:48:47.780
Yeah.

00:48:47.780 --> 00:48:51.459
I mean, AI governance is like a minefield at the moment because we're so early on.

00:48:53.379 --> 00:48:55.379
There's a combination of things happening, right?

00:48:55.379 --> 00:48:59.219
One is that there's constant flow of new things coming on the market.

00:48:59.219 --> 00:49:00.340
We've got this great new model.

00:49:00.340 --> 00:49:01.300
It does X, Y, and Z.

00:49:02.100 --> 00:49:06.739
At the same time, I think organizations are feeling a lot of urgency to do something with

00:49:06.739 --> 00:49:10.979
AI because they're looking around and saying, oh, look, everybody's talking about AI.

00:49:10.979 --> 00:49:14.500
So we have to do something or we'll be left behind.

00:49:15.699 --> 00:49:20.899
And that can create a challenging environment for professionals because I'm a huge believer,

00:49:20.899 --> 00:49:27.219
right, that you do something because there's an obvious benefit from doing it.

00:49:27.219 --> 00:49:31.219
Like you can see straight away, I'm taking on this project because if I get this right,

00:49:31.780 --> 00:49:33.459
there's this clear benefit from it.

00:49:34.100 --> 00:49:39.939
But AI can lead to a little bit of backwards logic, which is where leaders will say to people,

00:49:40.659 --> 00:49:44.260
find a way of using AI because everyone else is using it, right?

00:49:44.260 --> 00:49:48.899
And you should never with technology be told to find a way to use something.

00:49:48.899 --> 00:49:50.419
It should be obvious, right?

00:49:50.419 --> 00:49:52.260
It should be very clear to you what the use is.

00:49:53.060 --> 00:49:56.820
So that puts a lot of professionals in awkward positions because they're kind of looking at

00:49:56.820 --> 00:49:58.979
this technology and saying, what are the ways that I can use it?

00:49:59.379 --> 00:50:04.260
And my first thing is, I think, when it comes to governance, I do think that organizations

00:50:04.260 --> 00:50:07.620
need to have a good view on, like, where is the value, right?

00:50:07.620 --> 00:50:12.260
Don't do 20 different things, all of which you're not sure the value of.

00:50:12.899 --> 00:50:18.100
Try to narrow it down very early on to two or three things that you think would be massively

00:50:18.100 --> 00:50:22.020
valuable and balance that with risk, right?

00:50:22.020 --> 00:50:27.780
Because AI can give you a lot of value, but there's a significant amount of risk involved

00:50:27.860 --> 00:50:28.419
with it as well.

00:50:29.540 --> 00:50:33.459
And the question is, like, if something was going to save you, like, several millions

00:50:33.459 --> 00:50:39.620
of dollars in cost, but there's a, like, 1% chance that something could go wrong that

00:50:39.620 --> 00:50:43.379
leads to a lawsuit that could cost you, like, several million dollars, right?

00:50:43.379 --> 00:50:44.500
You've got to kind of do that.

00:50:44.500 --> 00:50:45.860
You've got to work that balance out.

00:50:46.659 --> 00:50:50.739
So, you know, I'm not involved in AI governance myself.

00:50:50.739 --> 00:50:51.780
It's a bit of a minefield.

00:50:51.780 --> 00:50:56.419
But I do think that you need a good business head to think about, like, what is the genuine

00:50:57.060 --> 00:51:02.419
value and not waste too much time on speculative stuff and make sure you've got people who

00:51:02.419 --> 00:51:04.659
really understand the risk and can evaluate the risk.

00:51:04.659 --> 00:51:07.219
Thank you.

